description:
quotient of the volume of oxygen and dry air, all volumes referring to the pressure and the temperature of the gas mixture.
dry air contains roughly (by volume) 78% nitrogen, 21% oxygen, 0.93% argon, 0.038% carbon dioxide, and small amounts of other gases.
